<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06137122 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06137122 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; BASEBALL; GAME; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Brett Butler was the hero of the Los Angeles Dodgers' 4-3 win over thevisiting Montreal Expos on Wednesday night, singling home the tie-breaking runin the seventh inning. Afterward, he was concerned about a teammate he hopeswill provide the heroics later this season.;    Butler, Los Angeles' centerfielder, cautioned right fielder Darryl Strawberry not to risk further injuryafter Strawberry crashed into the wall and hurt his left shoulder making acatch in the seventh inning.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  STRAWBERRY INJURED IN L.A. WIN  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  N.L. Roundup  </MEMO><TEXT>     Strawberry finished the inning but left the game in the eighth and went toa hospital for precautionary X-rays. The injury wasn't thought to be serious,and the team's assistant trainer, Charlie Strasser, said it was probably justa bruise or a sprain.;    &quot;When (Manager) Tommy Lasorda and Strasser came outto check him, Darryl said the shoulder was OK,&quot; Butler said. &quot;But after theyleft, I asked him and he said, 'No, I'm hurting.';    &quot;I told him he should goout now, but he didn't. Darryl doesn't need to be a hero now; it's not thatthis is unimportant, but it's only May and we'll need him a little furtherdown the road.&quot;;    The victory was the Dodgers' third straight, giving them asweep of the series against the Expos and moving them atop the N.L. Weststandings.; METS 7, PADRES 1: Dwight Gooden pitched a seven-hitter and NewYork used home runs by slumping Dave Magadan and Kevin McReynolds to win inSan Diego.; PIRATES 8, ASTROS 7: Don Slaught's pinch-hit, three-run triplesnapped an eighth-inning tie as Pittsburgh rallied to win in Houston despite18 hits by the Astros.; CUBS 6, BRAVES 1: In Chicago, Luis Salazar broke aseventh-inning tie with a two-run homer and Chicago knocked Atlanta out offirst place in the N.L. West.; CARDINALS 8, REDS 2: Bernard Gilkey broke asixth-inning tie with a home run and Rex Hudler hit a two-run double later inthe inning as host St. Louis beat Cincinnati.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910516  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  May  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4G  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  342  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday May 16, 199100137122,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>